105 //===========================================================================
106 // returns the surface area of the given face
107 //
108 // Parameter: -
109 // Returns: -
110 // Changes Globals: -
111 //===========================================================================
112 float AAS_FaceArea(aas_face_t *face)
113 {
114  int i, edgenum, side;
115  float total;
116  vec_t *v;
117  vec3_t d1, d2, cross;
118  aas_edge_t *edge;
119 
120  edgenum = aasworld.edgeindex[face->firstedge];
121  side = edgenum < 0;
122  edge = &aasworld.edges[abs(edgenum)];
123  v = aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[side]];
124 
125  total = 0;
126  for (i = 1; i < face->numedges - 1; i++)
127  {
128  edgenum = aasworld.edgeindex[face->firstedge + i];
129  side = edgenum < 0;
130  edge = &aasworld.edges[abs(edgenum)];
131  VectorSubtract(aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[side]], v, d1);
132  VectorSubtract(aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[!side]], v, d2);
133  CrossProduct(d1, d2, cross);
134  total += 0.5 * VectorLength(cross);
135  } //end for
136  return total;
137 } //end of the function AAS_FaceArea
138 //===========================================================================
139 // returns the volume of an area
140 //
141 // Parameter: -
142 // Returns: -
143 // Changes Globals: -
144 //===========================================================================
145 float AAS_AreaVolume(int areanum)
146 {
147  int i, edgenum, facenum, side;
148  vec_t d, a, volume;
149  vec3_t corner;
150  aas_plane_t *plane;
151  aas_edge_t *edge;
152  aas_face_t *face;
153  aas_area_t *area;
154 
155  area = &aasworld.areas[areanum];
156  facenum = aasworld.faceindex[area->firstface];
157  face = &aasworld.faces[abs(facenum)];
158  edgenum = aasworld.edgeindex[face->firstedge];
159  edge = &aasworld.edges[abs(edgenum)];
160  //
161  VectorCopy(aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[0]], corner);
162 
163  //make tetrahedrons to all other faces
164  volume = 0;
165  for (i = 0; i < area->numfaces; i++)
166  {
167  facenum = abs(aasworld.faceindex[area->firstface + i]);
168  face = &aasworld.faces[facenum];
169  side = face->backarea != areanum;
170  plane = &aasworld.planes[face->planenum ^ side];
171  d = -(DotProduct (corner, plane->normal) - plane->dist);
172  a = AAS_FaceArea(face);
173  volume += d * a;
174  } //end for
175 
176  volume /= 3;
177  return volume;
178 } //end of the function AAS_AreaVolume

185 int AAS_BestReachableLinkArea(aas_link_t *areas)
186 {
187  aas_link_t *link;
188 
189  for (link = areas; link; link = link->next_area)
190  {
191  if (AAS_AreaGrounded(link->areanum) || AAS_AreaSwim(link->areanum))
192  {
193  return link->areanum;
194  } //end if
195  } //end for
196  //
197  for (link = areas; link; link = link->next_area)
198  {
199  if (link->areanum) return link->areanum;
200  //FIXME: this is a bad idea when the reachability is not yet
201  // calculated when the level items are loaded
202  if (AAS_AreaReachability(link->areanum))
203  return link->areanum;
204  } //end for
205  return 0;
206 } //end of the function AAS_BestReachableLinkArea

213 int AAS_GetJumpPadInfo(int ent, vec3_t areastart, vec3_t absmins, vec3_t absmaxs, vec3_t velocity)
214 {
215  int modelnum, ent2;
216  float speed, height, gravity, time, dist, forward;
217  vec3_t origin, angles, teststart, ent2origin;
218  aas_trace_t trace;
219  char model[MAX_EPAIRKEY];
220  char target[MAX_EPAIRKEY], targetname[MAX_EPAIRKEY];
221 
222  //
223  AAS_FloatForBSPEpairKey(ent, "speed", &speed);
224  if (!speed) speed = 1000;
225  VectorClear(angles);
226  //get the mins, maxs and origin of the model
227  AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "model", model, MAX_EPAIRKEY);
228  if (model[0]) modelnum = atoi(model+1);
229  else modelnum = 0;
230  AAS_BSPModelMinsMaxsOrigin(modelnum, angles, absmins, absmaxs, origin);
231  VectorAdd(origin, absmins, absmins);
232  VectorAdd(origin, absmaxs, absmaxs);
233  VectorAdd(absmins, absmaxs, origin);
234  VectorScale (origin, 0.5, origin);
235 
236  //get the start areas
237  VectorCopy(origin, teststart);
238  teststart[2] += 64;
239  trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(teststart, origin, PRESENCE_CROUCH, -1);
240  if (trace.startsolid)
241  {
242  botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "trigger_push start solid\n");
243  VectorCopy(origin, areastart);
244  } //end if
245  else
246  {
247  VectorCopy(trace.endpos, areastart);
248  } //end else
249  areastart[2] += 0.125;
250  //
251  //AAS_DrawPermanentCross(origin, 4, 4);
252  //get the target entity
253  AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "target", target, MAX_EPAIRKEY);
254  for (ent2 = AAS_NextBSPEntity(0); ent2; ent2 = AAS_NextBSPEntity(ent2))
255  {
256  if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent2, "targetname", targetname, MAX_EPAIRKEY)) continue;
257  if (!strcmp(targetname, target)) break;
258  } //end for
259  if (!ent2)
260  {
261  botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "trigger_push without target entity %s\n", target);
262  return qfalse;
263  } //end if
264  AAS_VectorForBSPEpairKey(ent2, "origin", ent2origin);
265  //
266  height = ent2origin[2] - origin[2];
267  gravity = aassettings.phys_gravity;
268  time = sqrt( height / ( 0.5 * gravity ) );
269  if (!time)
270  {
271  botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "trigger_push without time\n");
272  return qfalse;
273  } //end if
274  // set s.origin2 to the push velocity
275  VectorSubtract ( ent2origin, origin, velocity);
276  dist = VectorNormalize( velocity);
277  forward = dist / time;
278  //FIXME: why multiply by 1.1
279  forward *= 1.1f;
280  VectorScale(velocity, forward, velocity);
281  velocity[2] = time * gravity;
282  return qtrue;
283 } //end of the function AAS_GetJumpPadInfo

290 int AAS_BestReachableFromJumpPadArea(vec3_t origin, vec3_t mins, vec3_t maxs)
291 {
292  int ent, bot_visualizejumppads, bestareanum;
293  float volume, bestareavolume;
294  vec3_t areastart, cmdmove, bboxmins, bboxmaxs;
295  vec3_t absmins, absmaxs, velocity;
296  aas_clientmove_t move;
297  aas_link_t *areas, *link;
298  char classname[MAX_EPAIRKEY];
299 
300 #ifdef BSPC
301  bot_visualizejumppads = 0;
302 #else
303  bot_visualizejumppads = LibVarValue("bot_visualizejumppads", "0");
304 #endif
305  VectorAdd(origin, mins, bboxmins);
306  VectorAdd(origin, maxs, bboxmaxs);
307  for (ent = AAS_NextBSPEntity(0); ent; ent = AAS_NextBSPEntity(ent))
308  {
309  if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "classname", classname, MAX_EPAIRKEY)) continue;
310  if (strcmp(classname, "trigger_push")) continue;
311  //
312  if (!AAS_GetJumpPadInfo(ent, areastart, absmins, absmaxs, velocity)) continue;
313  //get the areas the jump pad brush is in
314  areas = AAS_LinkEntityClientBBox(absmins, absmaxs, -1, PRESENCE_CROUCH);
315  for (link = areas; link; link = link->next_area)
316  {
317  if (AAS_AreaJumpPad(link->areanum)) break;
318  } //end for
319  if (!link)
320  {
321  botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "trigger_push not in any jump pad area\n");
322  AAS_UnlinkFromAreas(areas);
323  continue;
324  } //end if
325  //
326  //botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "found a trigger_push with velocity %f %f %f\n", velocity[0], velocity[1], velocity[2]);
327  //
328  VectorSet(cmdmove, 0, 0, 0);
329  Com_Memset(&move, 0, sizeof(aas_clientmove_t));
330  AAS_ClientMovementHitBBox(&move, -1, areastart, PRESENCE_NORMAL, qfalse,
331  velocity, cmdmove, 0, 30, 0.1f, bboxmins, bboxmaxs, bot_visualizejumppads);
332  if (move.frames < 30)
333  {
334  bestareanum = 0;
335  bestareavolume = 0;
336  for (link = areas; link; link = link->next_area)
337  {
338  if (!AAS_AreaJumpPad(link->areanum)) continue;
339  volume = AAS_AreaVolume(link->areanum);
340  if (volume >= bestareavolume)
341  {
342  bestareanum = link->areanum;
343  bestareavolume = volume;
344  } //end if
345  } //end if
346  AAS_UnlinkFromAreas(areas);
347  return bestareanum;
348  } //end if
349  AAS_UnlinkFromAreas(areas);
350  } //end for
351  return 0;
352 } //end of the function AAS_BestReachableFromJumpPadArea

359 int AAS_BestReachableArea(vec3_t origin, vec3_t mins, vec3_t maxs, vec3_t goalorigin)
360 {
361  int areanum, i, j, k, l;
362  aas_link_t *areas;
363  vec3_t absmins, absmaxs;
364  //vec3_t bbmins, bbmaxs;
365  vec3_t start, end;
366  aas_trace_t trace;
367 
368  if (!aasworld.loaded)
369  {
370  botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "AAS_BestReachableArea: aas not loaded\n");
371  return 0;
372  } //end if
373  //find a point in an area
374  VectorCopy(origin, start);
375  areanum = AAS_PointAreaNum(start);
376  //while no area found fudge around a little
377  for (i = 0; i < 5 && !areanum; i++)
378  {
379  for (j = 0; j < 5 && !areanum; j++)
380  {
381  for (k = -1; k <= 1 && !areanum; k++)
382  {
383  for (l = -1; l <= 1 && !areanum; l++)
384  {
385  VectorCopy(origin, start);
386  start[0] += (float) j * 4 * k;
387  start[1] += (float) j * 4 * l;
388  start[2] += (float) i * 4;
389  areanum = AAS_PointAreaNum(start);
390  } //end for
391  } //end for
392  } //end for
393  } //end for
394  //if an area was found
395  if (areanum)
396  {
397  //drop client bbox down and try again
398  VectorCopy(start, end);
399  start[2] += 0.25;
400  end[2] -= 50;
401  trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(start, end, PRESENCE_CROUCH, -1);
402  if (!trace.startsolid)
403  {
404  areanum = AAS_PointAreaNum(trace.endpos);
405  VectorCopy(trace.endpos, goalorigin);
406  //FIXME: cannot enable next line right now because the reachability
407  // does not have to be calculated when the level items are loaded
408  //if the origin is in an area with reachability
409  //if (AAS_AreaReachability(areanum)) return areanum;
410  if (areanum) return areanum;
411  } //end if
412  else
413  {
414  //it can very well happen that the AAS_PointAreaNum function tells that
415  //a point is in an area and that starting an AAS_TraceClientBBox from that
416  //point will return trace.startsolid qtrue
417 #if 0
418  if (AAS_PointAreaNum(start))
419  {
420  Log_Write("point %f %f %f in area %d but trace startsolid", start[0], start[1], start[2], areanum);
421  AAS_DrawPermanentCross(start, 4, LINECOLOR_RED);
422  } //end if
423  botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "AAS_BestReachableArea: start solid\n");
424 #endif
425  VectorCopy(start, goalorigin);
426  return areanum;
427  } //end else
428  } //end if
429  //
430  //AAS_PresenceTypeBoundingBox(PRESENCE_CROUCH, bbmins, bbmaxs);
431  //NOTE: the goal origin does not have to be in the goal area
432  // because the bot will have to move towards the item origin anyway
433  VectorCopy(origin, goalorigin);
434  //
435  VectorAdd(origin, mins, absmins);
436  VectorAdd(origin, maxs, absmaxs);
437  //add bounding box size
438  //VectorSubtract(absmins, bbmaxs, absmins);
439  //VectorSubtract(absmaxs, bbmins, absmaxs);
440  //link an invalid (-1) entity
441  areas = AAS_LinkEntityClientBBox(absmins, absmaxs, -1, PRESENCE_CROUCH);
442  //get the reachable link area
443  areanum = AAS_BestReachableLinkArea(areas);
444  //unlink the invalid entity
445  AAS_UnlinkFromAreas(areas);
446  //
447  return areanum;
448 } //end of the function AAS_BestReachableArea

455 void AAS_SetupReachabilityHeap(void)
456 {
457  int i;
458 
459  reachabilityheap = (aas_lreachability_t *) GetClearedMemory(
460  AAS_MAX_REACHABILITYSIZE * sizeof(aas_lreachability_t));
461  for (i = 0; i < AAS_MAX_REACHABILITYSIZE-1; i++)
462  {
463  reachabilityheap[i].next = &reachabilityheap[i+1];
464  } //end for
465  reachabilityheap[AAS_MAX_REACHABILITYSIZE-1].next = NULL;
466  nextreachability = reachabilityheap;
467  numlreachabilities = 0;
468 } //end of the function AAS_InitReachabilityHeap

487 aas_lreachability_t *AAS_AllocReachability(void)
488 {
489  aas_lreachability_t *r;
490 
491  if (!nextreachability) return NULL;
492  //make sure the error message only shows up once
493  if (!nextreachability->next) AAS_Error("AAS_MAX_REACHABILITYSIZE\n");
494  //
495  r = nextreachability;
496  nextreachability = nextreachability->next;
497  numlreachabilities++;
498  return r;

538 float AAS_AreaGroundFaceArea(int areanum)
539 {
540  int i;

543  aas_face_t *face;
544 
545  total = 0;
546  area = &aasworld.areas[areanum];
547  for (i = 0; i < area->numfaces; i++)
548  {
549  face = &aasworld.faces[abs(aasworld.faceindex[area->firstface + i])];
550  if (!(face->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
551  //
552  total += AAS_FaceArea(face);
553  } //end for
554  return total;
555 } //end of the function AAS_AreaGroundFaceArea
556 //===========================================================================
557 // returns the center of a face
558 //
559 // Parameter: -
560 // Returns: -
561 // Changes Globals: -
562 //===========================================================================
563 void AAS_FaceCenter(int facenum, vec3_t center)
564 {
565  int i;
566  float scale;
567  aas_face_t *face;
568  aas_edge_t *edge;
569 
570  face = &aasworld.faces[facenum];
571 
572  VectorClear(center);
573  for (i = 0; i < face->numedges; i++)
574  {
575  edge = &aasworld.edges[abs(aasworld.edgeindex[face->firstedge + i])];
576  VectorAdd(center, aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[0]], center);
577  VectorAdd(center, aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[1]], center);
578  } //end for
579  scale = 0.5 / face->numedges;
580  VectorScale(center, scale, center);
581 } //end of the function AAS_FaceCenter
582 //===========================================================================
583 // returns the maximum distance a player can fall before being damaged
584 // damage = deltavelocity*deltavelocity * 0.0001
585 //
586 // Parameter: -
587 // Returns: -
588 // Changes Globals: -
589 //===========================================================================
590 int AAS_FallDamageDistance(void)
591 {
592  float maxzvelocity, gravity, t;
593 
594  maxzvelocity = sqrt(30 * 10000);
595  gravity = aassettings.phys_gravity;
596  t = maxzvelocity / gravity;
597  return 0.5 * gravity * t * t;
598 } //end of the function AAS_FallDamageDistance
599 //===========================================================================
600 // distance = 0.5 * gravity * t * t
601 // vel = t * gravity
602 // damage = vel * vel * 0.0001
603 //
604 // Parameter: -
605 // Returns: -
606 // Changes Globals: -
607 //===========================================================================
608 float AAS_FallDelta(float distance)
609 {
610  float t, delta, gravity;
611 
612  gravity = aassettings.phys_gravity;
613  t = sqrt(fabs(distance) * 2 / gravity);
614  delta = t * gravity;
615  return delta * delta * 0.0001;
616 } //end of the function AAS_FallDelta
617 //===========================================================================
618 //
619 // Parameter: -
620 // Returns: -
621 // Changes Globals: -
622 //===========================================================================
623 float AAS_MaxJumpHeight(float phys_jumpvel)
624 {
625  float phys_gravity;
626 
627  phys_gravity = aassettings.phys_gravity;
628  //maximum height a player can jump with the given initial z velocity
629  return 0.5 * phys_gravity * (phys_jumpvel / phys_gravity) * (phys_jumpvel / phys_gravity);
630 } //end of the function MaxJumpHeight

637 //===========================================================================
638 float AAS_MaxJumpDistance(float phys_jumpvel)
639 {
640  float phys_gravity, phys_maxvelocity, t;
641 
642  phys_gravity = aassettings.phys_gravity;
643  phys_maxvelocity = aassettings.phys_maxvelocity;
644  //time a player takes to fall the height
645  t = sqrt(aassettings.rs_maxjumpfallheight / (0.5 * phys_gravity));
646  //maximum distance
647  return phys_maxvelocity * (t + phys_jumpvel / phys_gravity);
648 } //end of the function AAS_MaxJumpDistance

828 //===========================================================================

835 int AAS_Reachability_Swim(int area1num, int area2num)
836 {
837  int i, j, face1num, face2num, side1;
838  aas_area_t *area1, *area2;
839  aas_lreachability_t *lreach;
840  aas_face_t *face1;

893  areareachability[area1num] = lreach;
894  reach_swim++;
895  return qtrue;
896  } //end if
897  } //end if
898  } //end for
899  } //end for

902 //===========================================================================
903 // searches for reachabilities between adjacent areas with equal floor
904 // heights
905 //
906 // Parameter: -
907 // Returns: -
908 // Changes Globals: -
909 //===========================================================================
910 int AAS_Reachability_EqualFloorHeight(int area1num, int area2num)
911 {
912  int i, j, edgenum, edgenum1, edgenum2, foundreach, side;
913  float height, bestheight, length, bestlength;
914  vec3_t dir, start, end, normal, invgravity, gravitydirection = {0, 0, -1};
915  vec3_t edgevec;
916  aas_area_t *area1, *area2;
917  aas_face_t *face1, *face2;
918  aas_edge_t *edge;
919  aas_plane_t *plane2;
920  aas_lreachability_t lr, *lreach;
921 
922  if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(area1num) || !AAS_AreaGrounded(area2num)) return qfalse;
923 
924  area1 = &aasworld.areas[area1num];
925  area2 = &aasworld.areas[area2num];
926  //if the areas are not near enough in the x-y direction
927  for (i = 0; i < 2; i++)
928  {
929  if (area1->mins[i] > area2->maxs[i] + 10) return qfalse;
930  if (area1->maxs[i] < area2->mins[i] - 10) return qfalse;
931  } //end for
932  //if area 2 is too high above area 1
933  if (area2->mins[2] > area1->maxs[2]) return qfalse;
934  //
935  VectorCopy(gravitydirection, invgravity);
936  VectorInverse(invgravity);
937  //
938  bestheight = 99999;
939  bestlength = 0;
940  foundreach = qfalse;
941  Com_Memset(&lr, 0, sizeof(aas_lreachability_t)); //make the compiler happy
942  //
943  //check if the areas have ground faces with a common edge
944  //if existing use the lowest common edge for a reachability link
945  for (i = 0; i < area1->numfaces; i++)
946  {
947  face1 = &aasworld.faces[abs(aasworld.faceindex[area1->firstface + i])];
948  if (!(face1->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
949  //
950  for (j = 0; j < area2->numfaces; j++)
951  {
952  face2 = &aasworld.faces[abs(aasworld.faceindex[area2->firstface + j])];
953  if (!(face2->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
954  //if there is a common edge
955  for (edgenum1 = 0; edgenum1 < face1->numedges; edgenum1++)
956  {
957  for (edgenum2 = 0; edgenum2 < face2->numedges; edgenum2++)
958  {
959  if (abs(aasworld.edgeindex[face1->firstedge + edgenum1]) !=
960  abs(aasworld.edgeindex[face2->firstedge + edgenum2]))
961  continue;
962  edgenum = aasworld.edgeindex[face1->firstedge + edgenum1];
963  side = edgenum < 0;
964  edge = &aasworld.edges[abs(edgenum)];
965  //get the length of the edge
966  VectorSubtract(aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[1]],
967  aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[0]], dir);
968  length = VectorLength(dir);
969  //get the start point
970  VectorAdd(aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[0]],
971  aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[1]], start);
972  VectorScale(start, 0.5, start);
973  VectorCopy(start, end);
974  //get the end point several units inside area2
975  //and the start point several units inside area1
976  //NOTE: normal is pointing into area2 because the
977  //face edges are stored counter clockwise
978  VectorSubtract(aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[side]],
979  aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[!side]], edgevec);
980  plane2 = &aasworld.planes[face2->planenum];
981  CrossProduct(edgevec, plane2->normal, normal);
982  VectorNormalize(normal);
983  //
984  //VectorMA(start, -1, normal, start);
985  VectorMA(end, INSIDEUNITS_WALKEND, normal, end);
986  VectorMA(start, INSIDEUNITS_WALKSTART, normal, start);
987  end[2] += 0.125;
988  //
989  height = DotProduct(invgravity, start);
990  //NOTE: if there's nearby solid or a gap area after this area
991  //disabled this crap
992  //if (AAS_NearbySolidOrGap(start, end)) height += 200;
993  //NOTE: disabled because it disables reachabilities to very small areas
994  //if (AAS_PointAreaNum(end) != area2num) continue;
995  //get the longest lowest edge
996  if (height < bestheight ||
997  (height < bestheight + 1 && length > bestlength))
998  {
999  bestheight = height;
1000  bestlength = length;
1001  //create a new reachability link
1002  lr.areanum = area2num;
1003  lr.facenum = 0;
1004  lr.edgenum = edgenum;
1005  VectorCopy(start, lr.start);
1006  VectorCopy(end, lr.end);
1007  lr.traveltype = TRAVEL_WALK;
1008  lr.traveltime = 1;
1009  foundreach = qtrue;
1010  } //end if
1011  } //end for
1012  } //end for
1013  } //end for
1014  } //end for
1015  if (foundreach)
1016  {
1017  //create a new reachability link
1018  lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();
1019  if (!lreach) return qfalse;
1020  lreach->areanum = lr.areanum;
1021  lreach->facenum = lr.facenum;
1022  lreach->edgenum = lr.edgenum;
1023  VectorCopy(lr.start, lreach->start);
1024  VectorCopy(lr.end, lreach->end);
1025  lreach->traveltype = lr.traveltype;
1026  lreach->traveltime = lr.traveltime;
1027  lreach->next = areareachability[area1num];
1028  areareachability[area1num] = lreach;
1029  //if going into a crouch area
1030  if (!AAS_AreaCrouch(area1num) && AAS_AreaCrouch(area2num))
1031  {
1032  lreach->traveltime += aassettings.rs_startcrouch;
1033  } //end if
1034  /*
1035  //NOTE: if there's nearby solid or a gap area after this area
1036  if (!AAS_NearbySolidOrGap(lreach->start, lreach->end))
1037  {
1038  lreach->traveltime += 100;
1039  } //end if
1040  */
1041  //avoid rather small areas
1042  //if (AAS_AreaGroundFaceArea(lreach->areanum) < 500) lreach->traveltime += 100;
1043  //
1044  reach_equalfloor++;
1045  return qtrue;
1046  } //end if
1047  return qfalse;
1048 } //end of the function AAS_Reachability_EqualFloorHeight
1049 //===========================================================================
1050 // searches step, barrier, waterjump and walk off ledge reachabilities
1051 //
1052 // Parameter: -
1053 // Returns: -
1054 // Changes Globals: -
1055 //===========================================================================
1056 int AAS_Reachability_Step_Barrier_WaterJump_WalkOffLedge(int area1num, int area2num)
1057 {
1058  int i, j, k, l, edge1num, edge2num, areas[10], numareas;
1059  int ground_bestarea2groundedgenum, ground_foundreach;
1060  int water_bestarea2groundedgenum, water_foundreach;
1061  int side1, area1swim, faceside1, groundface1num;
1062  float dist, dist1, dist2, diff, ortdot;
1063  //float invgravitydot;
1064  float x1, x2, x3, x4, y1, y2, y3, y4, tmp, y;
1065  float length, ground_bestlength, water_bestlength, ground_bestdist, water_bestdist;
1066  vec3_t v1, v2, v3, v4, tmpv, p1area1, p1area2, p2area1, p2area2;
1067  vec3_t normal, ort, edgevec, start, end, dir;
1068  vec3_t ground_beststart = {0, 0, 0}, ground_bestend = {0, 0, 0}, ground_bestnormal = {0, 0, 0};
1069  vec3_t water_beststart = {0, 0, 0}, water_bestend = {0, 0, 0}, water_bestnormal = {0, 0, 0};
1070  vec3_t invgravity = {0, 0, 1};
1071  vec3_t testpoint;
1072  aas_plane_t *plane;
1073  aas_area_t *area1, *area2;
1074  aas_face_t *groundface1, *groundface2;
1075  aas_edge_t *edge1, *edge2;
1076  aas_lreachability_t *lreach;
1077  aas_trace_t trace;
1078 
1079  //must be able to walk or swim in the first area
1080  if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(area1num) && !AAS_AreaSwim(area1num)) return qfalse;
1081  //
1082  if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(area2num) && !AAS_AreaSwim(area2num)) return qfalse;
1083  //
1084  area1 = &aasworld.areas[area1num];
1085  area2 = &aasworld.areas[area2num];
1086  //if the first area contains a liquid
1087  area1swim = AAS_AreaSwim(area1num);
1088  //if the areas are not near enough in the x-y direction
1089  for (i = 0; i < 2; i++)
1090  {
1091  if (area1->mins[i] > area2->maxs[i] + 10) return qfalse;
1092  if (area1->maxs[i] < area2->mins[i] - 10) return qfalse;
1093  } //end for
1094  //
1095  ground_foundreach = qfalse;
1096  ground_bestdist = 99999;
1097  ground_bestlength = 0;
1098  ground_bestarea2groundedgenum = 0;
1099  //
1100  water_foundreach = qfalse;
1101  water_bestdist = 99999;
1102  water_bestlength = 0;
1103  water_bestarea2groundedgenum = 0;
1104  //
1105  for (i = 0; i < area1->numfaces; i++)
1106  {
1107  groundface1num = aasworld.faceindex[area1->firstface + i];
1108  faceside1 = groundface1num < 0;
1109  groundface1 = &aasworld.faces[abs(groundface1num)];
1110  //if this isn't a ground face
1111  if (!(groundface1->faceflags & FACE_GROUND))
1112  {
1113  //if we can swim in the first area
1114  if (area1swim)
1115  {
1116  //face plane must be more or less horizontal
1117  plane = &aasworld.planes[groundface1->planenum ^ (!faceside1)];
1118  if (DotProduct(plane->normal, invgravity) < 0.7) continue;
1119  } //end if
1120  else
1121  {
1122  //if we can't swim in the area it must be a ground face
1123  continue;
1124  } //end else
1125  } //end if
1126  //
1127  for (k = 0; k < groundface1->numedges; k++)
1128  {
1129  edge1num = aasworld.edgeindex[groundface1->firstedge + k];
1130  side1 = (edge1num < 0);
1131  //NOTE: for water faces we must take the side area 1 is
1132  // on into account because the face is shared and doesn't
1133  // have to be oriented correctly
1134  if (!(groundface1->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) side1 = (side1 == faceside1);
1135  edge1num = abs(edge1num);
1136  edge1 = &aasworld.edges[edge1num];
1137  //vertexes of the edge
1138  VectorCopy(aasworld.vertexes[edge1->v[!side1]], v1);
1139  VectorCopy(aasworld.vertexes[edge1->v[side1]], v2);
1140  //get a vertical plane through the edge
1141  //NOTE: normal is pointing into area 2 because the
1142  //face edges are stored counter clockwise
1143  VectorSubtract(v2, v1, edgevec);
1144  CrossProduct(edgevec, invgravity, normal);
1145  VectorNormalize(normal);
1146  dist = DotProduct(normal, v1);
1147  //check the faces from the second area
1148  for (j = 0; j < area2->numfaces; j++)
1149  {
1150  groundface2 = &aasworld.faces[abs(aasworld.faceindex[area2->firstface + j])];
1151  //must be a ground face
1152  if (!(groundface2->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
1153  //check the edges of this ground face
1154  for (l = 0; l < groundface2->numedges; l++)
1155  {
1156  edge2num = abs(aasworld.edgeindex[groundface2->firstedge + l]);
1157  edge2 = &aasworld.edges[edge2num];
1158  //vertexes of the edge
1159  VectorCopy(aasworld.vertexes[edge2->v[0]], v3);
1160  VectorCopy(aasworld.vertexes[edge2->v[1]], v4);
1161  //check the distance between the two points and the vertical plane
1162  //through the edge of area1
1163  diff = DotProduct(normal, v3) - dist;
1164  if (diff < -0.1 || diff > 0.1) continue;
1165  diff = DotProduct(normal, v4) - dist;
1166  if (diff < -0.1 || diff > 0.1) continue;
1167  //
1168  //project the two ground edges into the step side plane
1169  //and calculate the shortest distance between the two
1170  //edges if they overlap in the direction orthogonal to
1171  //the gravity direction
1172  CrossProduct(invgravity, normal, ort);
1173  //invgravitydot = DotProduct(invgravity, invgravity);
1174  ortdot = DotProduct(ort, ort);
1175  //projection into the step plane
1176  //NOTE: since gravity is vertical this is just the z coordinate
1177  y1 = v1[2];//DotProduct(v1, invgravity) / invgravitydot;
1178  y2 = v2[2];//DotProduct(v2, invgravity) / invgravitydot;
1179  y3 = v3[2];//DotProduct(v3, invgravity) / invgravitydot;
1180  y4 = v4[2];//DotProduct(v4, invgravity) / invgravitydot;
1181  //
1182  x1 = DotProduct(v1, ort) / ortdot;
1183  x2 = DotProduct(v2, ort) / ortdot;
1184  x3 = DotProduct(v3, ort) / ortdot;
1185  x4 = DotProduct(v4, ort) / ortdot;
1186  //
1187  if (x1 > x2)
1188  {
1189  tmp = x1; x1 = x2; x2 = tmp;
1190  tmp = y1; y1 = y2; y2 = tmp;
1191  VectorCopy(v1, tmpv); VectorCopy(v2, v1); VectorCopy(tmpv, v2);
1192  } //end if
1193  if (x3 > x4)
1194  {
1195  tmp = x3; x3 = x4; x4 = tmp;
1196  tmp = y3; y3 = y4; y4 = tmp;
1197  VectorCopy(v3, tmpv); VectorCopy(v4, v3); VectorCopy(tmpv, v4);
1198  } //end if
1199  //if the two projected edge lines have no overlap
1200  if (x2 <= x3 || x4 <= x1)
1201  {
1202 // Log_Write("lines no overlap: from area %d to %d\r\n", area1num, area2num);
1203  continue;
1204  } //end if
1205  //if the two lines fully overlap

1276  {

1280  } //end else if
1281  else

2090 //===========================================================================
2091 // creates possible jump reachabilities between the areas
2092 //
2093 // The two closest points on the ground of the areas are calculated
2094 // One of the points will be on an edge of a ground face of area1 and
2095 // one on an edge of a ground face of area2.
2096 // If there is a range of closest points the point in the middle of this range
2097 // is selected.
2098 // Between these two points there must be one or more gaps.
2099 // If the gaps exist a potential jump is predicted.

2337  height = dir[2];
2338  dir[2] = 0;
2339  if ((traveltype & TRAVELTYPE_MASK) == TRAVEL_WALKOFFLEDGE && height > VectorLength(dir))
2340  {
2341  lreach->traveltime = aassettings.rs_startwalkoffledge + height * 50 / aassettings.phys_gravity;
2342  }
2343  else
2344  {
2345  lreach->traveltime = aassettings.rs_startjump + VectorDistance(bestend, beststart) * 240 / aassettings.phys_maxwalkvelocity;
2346  } //end if
2347  //
2348  if (!AAS_AreaJumpPad(area2num))
2349  {
2350  if (AAS_FallDelta(beststart[2] - bestend[2]) > aassettings.phys_falldelta5)
2351  {
2352  lreach->traveltime += aassettings.rs_falldamage5;
2353  } //end if
2354  else if (AAS_FallDelta(beststart[2] - bestend[2]) > aassettings.phys_falldelta10)
2355  {
2356  lreach->traveltime += aassettings.rs_falldamage10;
2357  } //end if
2358  } //end if
2359  lreach->next = areareachability[area1num];
2360  areareachability[area1num] = lreach;
2361  //
2362  if ((traveltype & TRAVELTYPE_MASK) == TRAVEL_JUMP)
2363  reach_jump++;
2364  else
2365  reach_walkoffledge++;
2366  } //end if
2367  return qfalse;
2368 } //end of the function AAS_Reachability_Jump
2369 //===========================================================================
2370 // create a possible ladder reachability from area1 to area2
2371 //
2372 // Parameter: -
2373 // Returns: -
2374 // Changes Globals: -
2375 //===========================================================================
2376 int AAS_Reachability_Ladder(int area1num, int area2num)
2377 {

2379  int face1num, face2num, ladderface1num = 0, ladderface2num = 0;
2380  int ladderface1vertical, ladderface2vertical, firstv;

2384  vec3_t mid, lowestpoint = {0, 0}, start, end, sharededgevec, dir;
2385  aas_area_t *area1, *area2;

2400

2438  } //end for

2440  } //end for
2441  } //end for
2442  } //end for
2443  //

2446  //get the middle of the shared edge

2448  firstv = sharededgenum < 0;

2459  //

2464  //NOTE: 32 because that's larger than 16 (bot bbox x,y)

2470  //there's only reachability between vertical ladder faces

2472  //if both vertical ladder faces

2491  areareachability[area1num] = lreach;
2492  //
2493  reach_ladder++;
2494  //create a new reachability link
2495  lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();
2496  if (!lreach) return qfalse;
2497  lreach->areanum = area1num;
2498  lreach->facenum = ladderface2num;
2499  lreach->edgenum = abs(sharededgenum);
2500  VectorCopy(area2point, lreach->start);
2501  //VectorCopy(area1point, lreach->end);
2502  VectorMA(area1point, -3, plane1->normal, lreach->end);
2503  lreach->traveltype = TRAVEL_LADDER;
2504  lreach->traveltime = 10;
2505  lreach->next = areareachability[area2num];
2506  areareachability[area2num] = lreach;
2507  //
2508  reach_ladder++;
2509  //
2510  return qtrue;
2511  } //end if
2512  //if the second ladder face is also a ground face
2513  //create ladder end (just ladder) reachability and
2514  //walk off a ladder (ledge) reachability

2531  //

2533  //create a new reachability link

2535  if (!lreach) return qfalse;
2536  lreach->areanum = area1num;
2537  lreach->facenum = ladderface2num;
2538  lreach->edgenum = abs(sharededgenum);

2540  VectorCopy(area1point, lreach->end);
2541  lreach->traveltype = TRAVEL_WALKOFFLEDGE;
2542  lreach->traveltime = 10;
2543  lreach->next = areareachability[area2num];
2544  areareachability[area2num] = lreach;
2545  //
2546  reach_walkoffledge++;
2547  //

2549  } //end if
2550  //

2570  } //end if

2572  //

2581  //

2600  {

2649 #endif //REACH_DEBUG
2650  } //end if

2722 //===========================================================================
2723 // create possible teleporter reachabilities
2724 // this is very game dependent.... :(
2725 //
2726 // classname = trigger_multiple or trigger_teleport
2727 // target = "t1"
2728 //
2729 // classname = target_teleporter
2730 // targetname = "t1"
2731 // target = "t2"
2732 //
2733 // classname = misc_teleporter_dest
2734 // targetname = "t2"
2735 //
2736 // Parameter: -
2737 // Returns: -
2738 // Changes Globals: -
2739 //===========================================================================
2740 void AAS_Reachability_Teleport(void)
2741 {

2753 
2754  for (ent = AAS_NextBSPEntity(0); ent; ent = AAS_NextBSPEntity(ent))

2769  origin[0], origin[1], origin[2]);
2770  continue;
2771  } //end if
2772  for (dest = AAS_NextBSPEntity(0); dest; dest = AAS_NextBSPEntity(dest))
2773  {
2774  if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(dest, "classname", classname, MAX_EPAIRKEY)) continue;
2775  if (!strcmp(classname, "target_teleporter"))
2776  {
2777  if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(dest, "targetname", targetname, MAX_EPAIRKEY)) continue;
2778  if (!strcmp(targetname, target))
2779  {
2780  break;
2781  } //end if
2782  } //end if
2783  } //end for
2784  if (!dest)
2785  {
2786  continue;
2787  } //end if
2788  if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(dest, "target", target, MAX_EPAIRKEY))
2789  {
2790  botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "target_teleporter without target\n");
2791  continue;
2792  } //end if
2793  } //end else
2794  else if (!strcmp(classname, "trigger_teleport"))
2795  {
2796  AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "model", model, MAX_EPAIRKEY);
2797 //#ifdef REACH_DEBUG
2798  botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "trigger_teleport model = \"%s\"\n", model);
2799 //#endif REACH_DEBUG
2800  VectorClear(angles);
2801  AAS_BSPModelMinsMaxsOrigin(atoi(model+1), angles, mins, maxs, origin);
2802  //
2803  if (!AAS_ValueForBSPEpairKey(ent, "target", target, MAX_EPAIRKEY))
2804  {
2805  botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "trigger_teleport at %1.0f %1.0f %1.0f without target\n",
2806  origin[0], origin[1], origin[2]);
2807  continue;
2808  } //end if
2809  } //end if
2810  else
2811  {
2812  continue;
2813  } //end else
2814  //
2815  for (dest = AAS_NextBSPEntity(0); dest; dest = AAS_NextBSPEntity(dest))
2816  {

2821  {
2822  if (!strcmp(targetname, target))
2823  {
2824  break;
2825  } //end if
2826  } //end if
2827  } //end for
2828  if (!dest)
2829  {
2830  botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "teleporter without misc_teleporter_dest (%s)\n", target);
2831  continue;
2832  } //end if
2833  if (!AAS_VectorForBSPEpairKey(dest, "origin", destorigin))
2834  {
2835  botimport.Print(PRT_ERROR, "teleporter destination (%s) without origin\n", target);
2836  continue;
2837  } //end if
2838  //
2839  area2num = AAS_PointAreaNum(destorigin);
2840  //if not teleported into a teleporter or into a jumppad

2846  if (trace.startsolid)

2876  velocity, cmdmove, 0, 30, 0.1f,
2877  SE_HITGROUND|SE_ENTERWATER|SE_ENTERSLIME|
2878  SE_ENTERLAVA|SE_HITGROUNDDAMAGE|SE_TOUCHJUMPPAD|SE_TOUCHTELEPORTER, 0, qfalse); //qtrue);
2879  area2num = AAS_PointAreaNum(move.endpos);
2880  if (move.stopevent & (SE_ENTERSLIME|SE_ENTERLAVA))
2881  {
2882  botimport.Print(PRT_WARNING, "teleported into slime or lava at dest %s\n", target);

3144 //
3145 // Parameter: -
3146 // Returns: -

3149 aas_lreachability_t *AAS_FindFaceReachabilities(vec3_t *facepoints, int numpoints, aas_plane_t *plane, int towardsface)
3150 {
3151  int i, j, k, l;
3152  int facenum, edgenum, bestfacenum;
3153  float *v1, *v2, *v3, *v4;
3154  float bestdist, speed, hordist, dist;
3155  vec3_t beststart = {0}, beststart2 = {0}, bestend = {0}, bestend2 = {0}, tmp, hordir, testpoint;
3156  aas_lreachability_t *lreach, *lreachabilities;
3157  aas_area_t *area;
3158  aas_face_t *face;
3159  aas_edge_t *edge;
3160  aas_plane_t *faceplane, *bestfaceplane;
3161 
3162  //
3163  lreachabilities = NULL;
3164  bestfacenum = 0;
3165  bestfaceplane = NULL;
3166  //
3167  for (i = 1; i < aasworld.numareas; i++)
3168  {
3169  area = &aasworld.areas[i];
3170  // get the shortest distance between one of the func_bob start edges and
3171  // one of the face edges of area1
3172  bestdist = 999999;
3173  for (j = 0; j < area->numfaces; j++)
3174  {
3175  facenum = aasworld.faceindex[area->firstface + j];
3176  face = &aasworld.faces[abs(facenum)];
3177  //if not a ground face
3178  if (!(face->faceflags & FACE_GROUND)) continue;
3179  //get the ground planes
3180  faceplane = &aasworld.planes[face->planenum];
3181  //
3182  for (k = 0; k < face->numedges; k++)
3183  {
3184  edgenum = abs(aasworld.edgeindex[face->firstedge + k]);
3185  edge = &aasworld.edges[edgenum];
3186  //calculate the minimum distance between the two edges
3187  v1 = aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[0]];
3188  v2 = aasworld.vertexes[edge->v[1]];
3189  //
3190  for (l = 0; l < numpoints; l++)
3191  {
3192  v3 = facepoints[l];
3193  v4 = facepoints[(l+1) % numpoints];
3194  dist = AAS_ClosestEdgePoints(v1, v2, v3, v4, faceplane, plane,
3195  beststart, bestend,
3196  beststart2, bestend2, bestdist);
3197  if (dist < bestdist)
3198  {
3199  bestfacenum = facenum;
3200  bestfaceplane = faceplane;
3201  bestdist = dist;
3202  } //end if
3203  } //end for
3204  } //end for
3205  } //end for
3206  //
3207  if (bestdist > 192) continue;
3208  //
3209  VectorMiddle(beststart, beststart2, beststart);
3210  VectorMiddle(bestend, bestend2, bestend);
3211  //
3212  if (!towardsface)
3213  {
3214  VectorCopy(beststart, tmp);
3215  VectorCopy(bestend, beststart);
3216  VectorCopy(tmp, bestend);
3217  } //end if
3218  //
3219  VectorSubtract(bestend, beststart, hordir);
3220  hordir[2] = 0;
3221  hordist = VectorLength(hordir);
3222  //
3223  if (hordist > 2 * AAS_MaxJumpDistance(aassettings.phys_jumpvel)) continue;
3224  //the end point should not be significantly higher than the start point
3225  if (bestend[2] - 32 > beststart[2]) continue;
3226  //don't fall down too far
3227  if (bestend[2] < beststart[2] - 128) continue;
3228  //the distance should not be too far
3229  if (hordist > 32)
3230  {
3231  //check for walk off ledge
3232  if (!AAS_HorizontalVelocityForJump(0, beststart, bestend, &speed)) continue;
3233  } //end if
3234  //
3235  beststart[2] += 1;
3236  bestend[2] += 1;
3237  //
3238  if (towardsface) VectorCopy(bestend, testpoint);
3239  else VectorCopy(beststart, testpoint);
3240  if (bestfaceplane != NULL)
3241  testpoint[2] = (bestfaceplane->dist - DotProduct(bestfaceplane->normal, testpoint)) / bestfaceplane->normal[2];
3242  else
3243  testpoint[2] = 0;
3244  //
3245  if (!AAS_PointInsideFace(bestfacenum, testpoint, 0.1f))
3246  {
3247  //if the faces are not overlapping then only go down
3248  if (bestend[2] - 16 > beststart[2]) continue;
3249  } //end if
3250  lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();
3251  if (!lreach) return lreachabilities;
3252  lreach->areanum = i;
3253  lreach->facenum = 0;
3254  lreach->edgenum = 0;
3255  VectorCopy(beststart, lreach->start);
3256  VectorCopy(bestend, lreach->end);
3257  lreach->traveltype = 0;
3258  lreach->traveltime = 0;
3259  lreach->next = lreachabilities;
3260  lreachabilities = lreach;
3261 #ifndef BSPC
3262  if (towardsface) AAS_PermanentLine(lreach->start, lreach->end, 1);
3263  else AAS_PermanentLine(lreach->start, lreach->end, 2);
3264 #endif
3265  } //end for
3266  return lreachabilities;
3267 } //end of the function AAS_FindFaceReachabilities

3774 //===========================================================================
3775 // never point at ground faces
3776 // always a higher and pretty far area
3777 //
3778 // Parameter: -
3779 // Returns: -
3780 // Changes Globals: -
3781 //===========================================================================
3782 int AAS_Reachability_Grapple(int area1num, int area2num)
3783 {
3784  int face2num, i, j, areanum, numareas, areas[20];
3785  float mingrappleangle, z, hordist;
3786  bsp_trace_t bsptrace;
3787  aas_trace_t trace;
3788  aas_face_t *face2;
3789  aas_area_t *area1, *area2;
3790  aas_lreachability_t *lreach;
3791  vec3_t areastart = {0, 0, 0}, facecenter, start, end, dir, down = {0, 0, -1};
3792  vec_t *v;
3793 
3794  //only grapple when on the ground or swimming
3795  if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(area1num) && !AAS_AreaSwim(area1num)) return qfalse;
3796  //don't grapple from a crouch area
3797  if (!(AAS_AreaPresenceType(area1num) & PRESENCE_NORMAL)) return qfalse;
3798  //NOTE: disabled area swim it doesn't work right
3799  if (AAS_AreaSwim(area1num)) return qfalse;
3800  //
3801  area1 = &aasworld.areas[area1num];
3802  area2 = &aasworld.areas[area2num];
3803  //don't grapple towards way lower areas
3804  if (area2->maxs[2] < area1->mins[2]) return qfalse;
3805  //
3806  VectorCopy(aasworld.areas[area1num].center, start);
3807  //if not a swim area
3808  if (!AAS_AreaSwim(area1num))
3809  {
3810  if (!AAS_PointAreaNum(start)) Log_Write("area %d center %f %f %f in solid?\r\n", area1num,
3811  start[0], start[1], start[2]);
3812  VectorCopy(start, end);
3813  end[2] -= 1000;
3814  trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(start, end, PRESENCE_CROUCH, -1);
3815  if (trace.startsolid) return qfalse;
3816  VectorCopy(trace.endpos, areastart);
3817  } //end if
3818  else
3819  {
3820  if (!(AAS_PointContents(start) & (CONTENTS_LAVA|CONTENTS_SLIME|CONTENTS_WATER))) return qfalse;
3821  } //end else
3822  //
3823  //start is now the start point
3824  //
3825  for (i = 0; i < area2->numfaces; i++)
3826  {
3827  face2num = aasworld.faceindex[area2->firstface + i];
3828  face2 = &aasworld.faces[abs(face2num)];
3829  //if it is not a solid face
3830  if (!(face2->faceflags & FACE_SOLID)) continue;
3831  //direction towards the first vertex of the face
3832  v = aasworld.vertexes[aasworld.edges[abs(aasworld.edgeindex[face2->firstedge])].v[0]];
3833  VectorSubtract(v, areastart, dir);
3834  //if the face plane is facing away
3835  if (DotProduct(aasworld.planes[face2->planenum].normal, dir) > 0) continue;
3836  //get the center of the face
3837  AAS_FaceCenter(face2num, facecenter);
3838  //only go higher up with the grapple
3839  if (facecenter[2] < areastart[2] + 64) continue;
3840  //only use vertical faces or downward facing faces
3841  if (DotProduct(aasworld.planes[face2->planenum].normal, down) < 0) continue;
3842  //direction towards the face center
3843  VectorSubtract(facecenter, areastart, dir);
3844  //
3845  z = dir[2];
3846  dir[2] = 0;
3847  hordist = VectorLength(dir);
3848  if (!hordist) continue;
3849  //if too far
3850  if (hordist > 2000) continue;
3851  //check the minimal angle of the movement
3852  mingrappleangle = 15; //15 degrees
3853  if (z / hordist < tan(2 * M_PI * mingrappleangle / 360)) continue;
3854  //
3855  VectorCopy(facecenter, start);
3856  VectorMA(facecenter, -500, aasworld.planes[face2->planenum].normal, end);
3857  //
3858  bsptrace = AAS_Trace(start, NULL, NULL, end, 0, CONTENTS_SOLID);
3859  //the grapple won't stick to the sky and the grapple point should be near the AAS wall
3860  if ((bsptrace.surface.flags & SURF_SKY) || (bsptrace.fraction * 500 > 32)) continue;
3861  //trace a full bounding box from the area center on the ground to
3862  //the center of the face
3863  VectorSubtract(facecenter, areastart, dir);
3864  VectorNormalize(dir);
3865  VectorMA(areastart, 4, dir, start);
3866  VectorCopy(bsptrace.endpos, end);
3867  trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(start, end, PRESENCE_NORMAL, -1);
3868  VectorSubtract(trace.endpos, facecenter, dir);
3869  if (VectorLength(dir) > 24) continue;
3870  //
3871  VectorCopy(trace.endpos, start);
3872  VectorCopy(trace.endpos, end);
3873  end[2] -= AAS_FallDamageDistance();
3874  trace = AAS_TraceClientBBox(start, end, PRESENCE_NORMAL, -1);
3875  if (trace.fraction >= 1) continue;
3876  //area to end in
3877  areanum = AAS_PointAreaNum(trace.endpos);
3878  //if not in lava or slime
3879  if (aasworld.areasettings[areanum].contents & (AREACONTENTS_SLIME|AREACONTENTS_LAVA))
3880  {
3881  continue;
3882  } //end if
3883  //do not go the the source area
3884  if (areanum == area1num) continue;
3885  //don't create reachabilities if they already exist
3886  if (AAS_ReachabilityExists(area1num, areanum)) continue;
3887  //only end in areas we can stand
3888  if (!AAS_AreaGrounded(areanum)) continue;
3889  //never go through cluster portals!!
3890  numareas = AAS_TraceAreas(areastart, bsptrace.endpos, areas, NULL, 20);
3891  if (numareas >= 20) continue;
3892  for (j = 0; j < numareas; j++)
3893  {
3894  if (aasworld.areasettings[areas[j]].contents & AREACONTENTS_CLUSTERPORTAL) break;
3895  } //end for
3896  if (j < numareas) continue;
3897  //create a new reachability link
3898  lreach = AAS_AllocReachability();
3899  if (!lreach) return qfalse;
3900  lreach->areanum = areanum;
3901  lreach->facenum = face2num;
3902  lreach->edgenum = 0;
3903  VectorCopy(areastart, lreach->start);
3904  //VectorCopy(facecenter, lreach->end);
3905  VectorCopy(bsptrace.endpos, lreach->end);

4342 // TRAVEL_SWIM 100%

4350 // TRAVEL_ROCKETJUMP 100% (currently limited towards areas with items)
4351 // TRAVEL_BFGJUMP 0% (currently disabled)
4352 // TRAVEL_JUMPPAD 100%
4353 // TRAVEL_FUNCBOB 100%
4354 //
4355 // Parameter: -
4356 // Returns: true if NOT finished
4357 // Changes Globals: -
4358 //===========================================================================
4359 int AAS_ContinueInitReachability(float time)
4360 {
4361  int i, j, todo, start_time;
4362  static float framereachability, reachability_delay;
4363  static int lastpercentage;
4364 
4365  if (!aasworld.loaded) return qfalse;
4366  //if reachability is calculated for all areas
4367  if (aasworld.numreachabilityareas >= aasworld.numareas + 2) return qfalse;
4368  //if starting with area 1 (area 0 is a dummy)
4369  if (aasworld.numreachabilityareas == 1)
4370  {
4371  botimport.Print(PRT_MESSAGE, "calculating reachability...\n");
4372  lastpercentage = 0;
4373  framereachability = 2000;
4374  reachability_delay = 1000;
4375  } //end if
4376  //number of areas to calculate reachability for this cycle
4377  todo = aasworld.numreachabilityareas + (int) framereachability;
4378  start_time = Sys_MilliSeconds();
4379  //loop over the areas
4380  for (i = aasworld.numreachabilityareas; i < aasworld.numareas && i < todo; i++)
4381  {
4382  aasworld.numreachabilityareas++;
4383  //only create jumppad reachabilities from jumppad areas
4384  if (aasworld.areasettings[i].contents & AREACONTENTS_JUMPPAD)
4385  {
4386  continue;
4387  } //end if
4388  //loop over the areas
4389  for (j = 1; j < aasworld.numareas; j++)
4390  {
4391  if (i == j) continue;
4392  //never create reachabilities from teleporter or jumppad areas to regular areas
4393  if (aasworld.areasettings[i].contents & (AREACONTENTS_TELEPORTER|AREACONTENTS_JUMPPAD))
4394  {
4395  if (!(aasworld.areasettings[j].contents & (AREACONTENTS_TELEPORTER|AREACONTENTS_JUMPPAD)))
4396  {
4397  continue;
4398  } //end if
4399  } //end if
4400  //if there already is a reachability link from area i to j
4401  if (AAS_ReachabilityExists(i, j)) continue;
4402  //check for a swim reachability
4403  if (AAS_Reachability_Swim(i, j)) continue;
4404  //check for a simple walk on equal floor height reachability
4405  if (AAS_Reachability_EqualFloorHeight(i, j)) continue;
4406  //check for step, barrier, waterjump and walk off ledge reachabilities
4407  if (AAS_Reachability_Step_Barrier_WaterJump_WalkOffLedge(i, j)) continue;
4408  //check for ladder reachabilities
4409  if (AAS_Reachability_Ladder(i, j)) continue;
4410  //check for a jump reachability
4411  if (AAS_Reachability_Jump(i, j)) continue;
4412  } //end for
4413  //never create these reachabilities from teleporter or jumppad areas
4414  if (aasworld.areasettings[i].contents & (AREACONTENTS_TELEPORTER|AREACONTENTS_JUMPPAD))
4415  {
4416  continue;
4417  } //end if
4418  //loop over the areas
4419  for (j = 1; j < aasworld.numareas; j++)
4420  {
4421  if (i == j) continue;
4422  //
4423  if (AAS_ReachabilityExists(i, j)) continue;
4424  //check for a grapple hook reachability
4425  if (calcgrapplereach) AAS_Reachability_Grapple(i, j);
4426  //check for a weapon jump reachability
4427  AAS_Reachability_WeaponJump(i, j);
4428  } //end for
4429  //if the calculation took more time than the max reachability delay
4430  if (Sys_MilliSeconds() - start_time > (int) reachability_delay) break;
4431  //
4432  if (aasworld.numreachabilityareas * 1000 / aasworld.numareas > lastpercentage) break;
4433  } //end for
4434  //
